 <text id="A7000T">
  <front id="d2">
   <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
    <p>J. Peague writes Matthew Pilson recommending a certain Mr. Greenlee for an unspecified
     teaching position. Peague attests to Mr. Greenlee's moral character.</p>
   </div1>
  </front>

  <body id="d4">
   <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
    <opener>
     <dateline>
      <date value="1857-08-15"><abbr expan="August">Aug.</abbr> 15. 1857</date>
     </dateline>
     <salute>Mr. Pilson Dear Sir</salute>
    </opener>

    <p>According to agreement, I inform you with pleasure that Mr. Greenlee will certainly teach the
     next session.</p>

    <p>And I am candid in recommending him to your patronage as both a gentleman + a Christian who I
     believe will be faithful in the moral and mental culture of those confided to his charge. For
     particulars see notices in Gazelle + Cen. Presbyterian</p>

    <closer>
     <salute>respectfully</salute>
     <signed>J. <unclear>Melaor</unclear> Peague</signed>
     <seg type="postscript">P.S. My kind regards, if you please to each of your family. J. P.</seg>
    </closer>
   </div1>
  </body>
 </text>
